<google_dorking_guide>
<title>GOOGLE DORKING AND ADVANCED SEARCH RECONNAISSANCE</title>

<critical>Google dorking leverages advanced search operators to discover sensitive information, exposed files, login panels, and vulnerable systems indexed by search engines. This passive reconnaissance technique reveals configuration files, backup data, admin interfaces, and security misconfigurations without direct target interaction. Search engines index what should remain hidden—exploit this asymmetry.</critical>

<scope>
- Advanced search operator mastery
- Sensitive file and directory discovery
- Login and admin panel enumeration
- Database and backup file exposure
- Error message and stack trace discovery
- Source code and configuration leakage
- Subdomain and infrastructure mapping
- Vulnerable application fingerprinting
- API key and credential exposure
- Cloud storage misconfiguration detection
</scope>

<methodology>
1. Identify target domains and related assets.
2. Enumerate subdomains and related infrastructure via search.
3. Discover exposed sensitive files and directories.
4. Find login panels, admin interfaces, and dashboards.
5. Locate error messages revealing technology stack.
6. Search for exposed credentials and API keys.
7. Identify vulnerable application versions.
8. Map cloud storage and third-party integrations.
9. Document findings and assess exposure severity.
10. Verify discoveries without triggering alerts.
</methodology>

<testing_techniques>
<core_operators>
{% raw %}
# Essential Google Search Operators

# Site-specific search
site:example.com                    # All indexed pages on domain
site:*.example.com                  # Include subdomains
site:example.com -www               # Exclude www subdomain

# File type discovery
filetype:pdf site:example.com       # PDF documents
filetype:doc OR filetype:docx       # Word documents
filetype:xls OR filetype:xlsx       # Excel spreadsheets
filetype:sql                        # SQL database dumps
filetype:log                        # Log files
filetype:bak OR filetype:backup     # Backup files
filetype:env                        # Environment files
filetype:config                     # Configuration files

# URL structure
inurl:admin site:example.com        # Admin in URL path
inurl:login site:example.com        # Login pages
inurl:wp-admin                      # WordPress admin
inurl:phpmyadmin                    # phpMyAdmin instances
inurl:api site:example.com          # API endpoints
allinurl:admin login                # Multiple terms in URL

# Page content
intitle:"index of"                  # Directory listings
intitle:"Dashboard"                 # Dashboard pages
allintitle:admin panel login        # Multiple title terms
intext:"sql syntax error"           # Error messages in body

# Combining operators
site:example.com filetype:pdf inurl:confidential
site:example.com intitle:admin -inurl:blog
site:*.example.com -site:www.example.com

# Exclusions
site:example.com -filetype:html     # Exclude HTML
site:example.com -inurl:news        # Exclude news section

# Cache and related
cache:example.com                   # Cached version
related:example.com                 # Similar sites
link:example.com                    # Pages linking to target
{% endraw %}
</core_operators>

